Class SummaryTaintWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.jimple.infoflow.methodSummary.taintWrappers.SummaryTaintWrapper

    public class SummaryTaintWrapper

      • getFlowSummariesForMethod

        protected ClassSummaries getFlowSummariesForMethod​(soot.jimple.Stmt stmt,
                                                   soot.SootMethod method,
                                                   Abstraction taintedAbs,
                                                   ByReferenceBoolean classSupported)
        Gets the flow summaries for the given method
        Parameters:
        stmt - (Optional) The invocation statement at which the given method is called. If this parameter is not null, it is used to find further potential callees if there are no flow summaries for the given method.
        method - The method for which to get the flow summaries
        taintedAbs - The tainted incoming abstraction
        classSupported - Outgoing parameter that informs the caller whether the callee class is supported, i.e., there is a summary configuration for that class
        Returns:
        The set of flow summaries for the given method if they exist, otherwise null. Note that this is a set of sets, one set per possible callee.

      • addCustomSinkTaint

        protected Taint addCustomSinkTaint​(MethodFlow flow,
                                   Taint taint,
                                   GapDefinition gap)
        Given the taint at the source and the flow, computes the taint at the sink. This method allows custom extensions to the taint wrapper. The default implementation always returns null.
        Parameters:
        flow - The flow between source and sink
        taint - The taint at the source statement
        gap - The gap at which the new flow will hold
        Returns:
        The taint at the sink that is obtained when applying the given flow to the given source taint

      • cutSubFields

        protected AccessPathFragment cutSubFields​(MethodFlow flow,
                                          AccessPathFragment accessPath)
        Cuts the given access path if required for the given method flow. This method can cut the incoming access path to shorter lengths or abandon the original access path altogether.
        Parameters:
        flow - The method flow specification
        accessPath - The remaining fields from the original access path
        Returns:
        The fields that shall be appended to the new access path. This is usually a prefix of the original remaining fields

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        true if the following fields shall be deleted, false otherwise
